-- 
CMC of Kenya Plans to Hire Agents to Sell Vehicles, Business Daily Reports

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-07T04:16:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/cmc-of-kenya-plans-to-hire-agents-to-sell-vehicles-business-daily-reports.html
CMC Holdings Ltd. (CMCH)  will spend as much
as 1 billion shillings ($11.5 million) on a turnaround strategy,
Business Daily reported, citing Managing Director Bill Lay.   The funds, which will be sourced from internal reserves,
will be used to hire agents to sell its vehicles in  Kenya  and
neighboring countries and to appoint people to offer repair and
maintenance services, the Nairobi-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  